wiki_section_title: U.S. Supreme Court

wiki_section_text: The Supreme Court of the United States is the nation 's highest court . Of the 112 justices to have served on the Supreme Court , [ 300 ] 12 have been Princetonians . Three current justices are Princeton graduates . Oliver Ellsworth was the second Chief Justice of the United States ; all others listed here were or are Associate Justices of the Supreme Court of the United States .

intro: This list of people associated with Princeton University includes graduates who have served in the national government of the United States.
